President Muhammadu Buhari has reacted to the death of All Progressives Congress (APC) stalwart, Arc. Umar Aliyu. A statement signed by his Spokesman, Garba Shehu, said that Buhari joins friends and associates to mourn the talented architect and loyal member of the party. The statement said that Buhari appreciates the deceased for always standing by the party and the government, “particularly dedicating his time and resources to mobilise for candidates during elections, and going further to build understanding with the electorate.” He prayed that the almighty God will receive the soul of the departed, and comfort his family.